l Buy\n2nd TRUST NOTES\non D. C. Improved Property.\nFEDERAL-AMERICAN COMPANY\n807 15th *t. N.W. NA. 8032\nIMPORTS OF FARM\nSTAPLES IN LEAD\nExceeded Exports by $204,320,000\nDuring Last Half Year,\nBureau Beports.\nP7 the Associated Press.\nThe Bureau of Agricultural Eco\nnomics reported that agricultural\ncommodities imported into the United\nStates during the last six months of\n1937 exceeded exports by $204,320,000.\nIt estimated the imports at $679.\n528.000, compared with $635,973,000\nduring the last half of 1936. Exports\nwere valued at $475,208,000 compared j\nwith $413,000,000 in 1936.\nThe bureau estimated imports\nclassed as competitive with domestic\nfarm products were valued at $305,\n816.000.\nThe bureau pointed out that ex\nports increased and imports declined\nin the late months of 1937, after the\nharvest of this country's good crops.\nIt predicted that \u201cin the absence of\nany unanticipated developments\u2019\u2019 this\ntrend would continue through the\ncurrent year.\nCommodities showing the largest in\ncrease in exports were cotton, wheat,\nthe feed grains, milled rice and flour.\nIncreases also were reported in lard,\ncanned milk, dried prunes, raisins, cot- j\ntonseed oil, soybeans, flue-cured to- I\nbacco. dried beans, peas, potatoes,j\nfresh tomatoes and canned vegetables, j\nCommodities showing increased im- i\nports included cattle, meats and meat1\nproducts and crude rubber.\nI. C. C. APPROVAL ASKED\nFOR MISSABE MERGER\nBy the Associated Press.\nThe Duluth. Missabe Iron Range\nRailway Co., the Duluth Iron Range\nRailroad Co. and the Interstate Trans\nfer Railway Co. asked Interstate Com\nmerce Commission permission yester\nday to merge into the Missabe.\nThe Missabe owns all the outstand\ning capital of the other roads. The\napplication said the proposed merger\nwould be in harmony with consoli\ndation recommendations of the I. C. C.\nC. E. Carlson of Duluth. Minn., is\npresident of all three of the companies, j\nI\nOFFICE,\nConvenien